  "market_context": "ES 1-hour chart showing a clearly defined consolidation range between approximately 4141 (range low) and 4186 (range high) with multiple highs forming at the top of the range, setting up a potential deviation and reversal scenario.",
  "key_observation": "Price displaced aggressively above the multiple highs at the top of the range and then aggressively displaced back into the range — a textbook box-setup deviation signaling a short opportunity at the retest of the highest body.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified the consolidation range on the 1H chart with range low ~4141 and range high ~4186 marked by multiple highs.",
    "Step 2: Observed aggressive displacement upward through the multiple highs (range high), purging buy-side liquidity above 4186.",
    "Step 3: Noted the equally aggressive displacement back down into the range — confirming a deviation rather than a genuine breakout.",
    "Step 4: Located the deviation/retest area and marked the highest body of the displacement candles as the entry zone (pink box ~4186–4198).",
    "Step 5: Planned a short entry on the retest of the deviation, with stop placed above the highest body of the displacement.",
    "Step 6: Defined the target as the opposite side of the range (~4141) or alternatively 2R before letting runners go for the full range target."
  ],
  "outcome": "Setup yielded over 5R according to the analyst's framing (2R taken first, runners targeting the opposite side of the range).",
  "lessons": "When price aggressively displaces out of a range and then aggressively displaces back in, treat it as a deviation. Use the highest body of the displacement as entry/stop reference and target the opposite side of the range for outsized R multiples.",
